Subject: Cannot provide access to StealthAudit for new Admin
Description: i added our new admin to the access section of StealthAudit. He is now listed as ad Administrator like the rest of us, but he cannot access the application.
What_We_Know__c: Customer has added the new user as an "Administrator". Not sure where exactly (to the machine? to the console?))
Next_Steps__c: Provided customer the steps of adding the new user to the proper role group in SQL and verify they have been added to the Access node in NEA Settings
Solution_Comment__c: User was added to the correct group with DBO so once we added them in the Access Node as an admin everything worked as expected
